evals.prompt:
A user reports that their custom plugin's lifecycle hook is not executing. The plugin is structured as:

```typescript
// packages/plugins/custom/src/lifecycle.ts
import { ApplicationLifecycle, ArtusApplication, Inject, ArtusInjectEnum } from '@artus/core';

export default class CustomLifecycle implements ApplicationLifecycle {
  @Inject(ArtusInjectEnum.Application)
  app: ArtusApplication;

  async willReady() {
    console.log('Custom plugin initializing...');
    // Initialization code
  }
}
```

The user says the console.log never appears. Diagnose the issue and provide the fix.

evals.expected_output:
Diagnosis: The lifecycle hook is missing two critical decorators:
1. @LifecycleHookUnit decorator on the class
2. @LifecycleHook decorator on the willReady method

Without these decorators, ArtusX cannot identify the class as a lifecycle unit and the method as a hook.

Fix: Add the decorators:

```typescript
import { LifecycleHookUnit, LifecycleHook, ApplicationLifecycle, ArtusApplication, Inject, ArtusInjectEnum } from '@artus/core';

@LifecycleHookUnit()  // <-- Required decorator
export default class CustomLifecycle implements ApplicationLifecycle {
  @Inject(ArtusInjectEnum.Application)
  app: ArtusApplication;

  @LifecycleHook()  // <-- Required decorator
  async willReady() {
    console.log('Custom plugin initializing...');
  }
}
```

Also verify:
1. lifecycle.ts is exported in index.ts
2. Plugin is registered in config/plugin.ts
